text: Since your browser does not support JavaScript,                 you must press the Continue button once to proceed.
Select an item below for more Transcript information and other services.
Order Official Transcript (Active Baker College User ID)
Click the "Order Official Transcript" image at the right.
Please wait approximately 4 weeks after the completion of the semester for your degree information to appear on your official transcript.
Degree posting can be viewed in MyBaker under Personal Info (link in top right corner).
Transcript requests are an automatic process and Baker College cannot hold requests for degrees or grades to be posted.
Transcripts can no longer be picked up at your local campus.

Within the ordering process, you can upload a document to send with an electronic transcript, or with a paper transcript sent by US Mail. (Previously, this option was only available to electronically sent transcripts.)

A hold on your Baker College account will not prevent you from requesting a transcript through Parchment Exchange.  However, Baker College will not be able to release your transcript until the hold is resolved.

Orders to release transcripts are processed through the online ordering system.  Transcripts sent online are fully secure and FERPA compliant.  Our PCI certification and third-party testing ensure that security is never in question.
If you have issues accessing your account, contact the ITSC for password assistance at
For questions or concerns regarding transcripts and other academic records, contact the Office of the Registrar by sending an email to:
Order Official Transcript (No active Baker College User ID)

If you do NOT have an active Baker College account, you can order an official transcript by clicking the "Order Official Transcript" image on the right.  You will need to provide some information so that we can identify you as a former student at Baker College.  Please have this information handy when you are ready to order your transcript.
The information below must match when you last attended Baker College:
Last 4 numbers of your Social Security number

If you complete the 'Create account' option, please note that the password you create cannot be changed by the Baker College ITSC. If you forget your password, the self-registration page will walk you through the password reset process without having to call the Baker College ITSC.
Baker College only provides unofficial transcripts to current students, or alumni with a My Baker account.
For current students, or alumni with a current My Baker College account, log in to My Baker using your current username and password.
Click on My Services tab across the top.
For current students, click on the Student Services Center, then Academic Services > Grade Information >
For alumni, click on the Alumni Center, then

Please wait approximately 4 weeks after the completion of the semester for your degree information to appear on your official transcript.  After the degree has been posted, degree information can be located in MyBaker under Personal Info (link in top right corner).
Baker College Registrars are here to help you meet your educational goals as quickly and efficiently as possible. We can help you with:
